        <num>19-7-41</num>
        <content>
          <p>In a proceeding under this article, the court, pursuant to Chapter 11 of Title 9, may order service upon a person outside the state upon a finding that there is a constitutionally permissible basis for jurisdiction over the person, including those enumerated in Article 3 of Chapter 11 of this title.</p>
          <p>(Code 1933, ยง 74-302, enacted by Ga. L. 1980, p. 1374, ยง 1; Ga. L. 1997, p. 1613, ยง 16.)</p>
